item.title: Pill Container
item.description: I am a stickler for using a little filament as possible in a print, so I designed my own streamlined travel pill box. The one shown in the images is printed at 80%, I recommend not going any smaller as the walls may become too thin. I used one that was 100% and it fit about twice as much as this one does, possibly more. I simply resized in cura and the model fits really well. The end is tapered so that it fits snugly to hold it shut, but the rest should slide smoothly once open. I modified the handle to be able to pull on it, the one in the picture was a bit too narrow.

item.title: Model Cam-Driven V8 Engine
item.description:
This is a 3d printable model of a V8 engine thats pistons are driven by cams on a drive shaft. It works by turning the drive shaft using the handle to rotate the cams and move the pistons up and down. Although not an accurate model of a real V8 engine, it is a fun desk toy and can help people understand the basics of an engine!

Hot glue or another adhesive is needed in assembly.

This project was in collaboration with Menachem Burger and Anton Voronov

item.title: Psyduck
item.description:
No supports. Only printed the Psyduck_Eyes_White.STL and Psyduck_Hair_Black.STL with a 5mm brim.

This is a remix of https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:2018766. I cut the lower portion of the body so that it could print on a flat surface without any supports. Just used super glue to put all pieces together at the end. Used a normal black pen to add the black dots inside of the white eyes. Re-faced all objects and exported files in the position that I printed them in. Also renamed the files in a Psyduck_BodyPart_Color.STL format.

item.title: BFG Ork Fleet Drop
item.description:
BFG Ork ships from Battlefleet Gothic: Armada 2. I wanted to print these and paint them, but the ones available for download online weren't cohesive with the tabletop game. So I learned how to extract them and assemble them in Blender, and now here they are.

Just about every option for a BFG tabletop Ork fleet, except for a space hulk. Scratch build that thing! (And ordinance markers. Some other time, perhaps.) I think they're mostly scaled ok for BFG, perhaps a little on the big side. Though in the game, model size is relative, so it should be fine.

Includes:
All 4 Battleship variants
Hammer Battlekroozer (custom assembly to look different from other ships)
Both prow options for Kill Kroozers
Both prow options for Terror Ships
All 4 escorts
Transport ship
2 variants of Roks
Space Station
and Defense Platform.

Enjoy, and happy printing!

item.title: MMDVM_HS_Dual_Hat Raspberry Pi 4 Case
item.description:
I purchased this board. https://www.aliexpress.com/item/1005003515392256.html (without the screen).

I couldn't find a case that I liked for the MMDVM_HS_Dual_Hat so I designed one for the Raspberry Pi 4.

STEP and STL files are included if you would like to make any modifications to the model.

I assemble mine with 4x M2.5x22mm screws. M2.5x25mm will also work. These are the ones that I use. https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07PPC173T. I use the same screws for my other Hotspot case.
